Applicable Terms and Conditions for this Docker image

1. Definitions

   “Global Synchronizer” means a decentralized synchronization domain for the Canton Network referred to as the Global Synchronizer; the Global Synchronizer is decentrally operated, with each Super Validator operating an instance of the Global Synchronizer software and with their actions mediated through the Global Synchronizer’s consensus protocol.

   “License” means this Applicable Terms and Conditions for this Docker image as set forth herein.

   “You” or “Your” means the individual or legal entity that is accessing Software through this Docker image.

   “Digital Asset” means Digital Asset (Switzerland) GmbH.

   “Purpose” means acting as a Super Validator or Validator.

   “Software” means any goods, licensed materials, documentation, or software (including object and/or source code) made available for download by Digital Asset via this Docker image.

   “Super Validator” means an entity that operates an instance of the Global Synchronizer software and has been approved to do so through the Global Synchronizer’s governance protocol.

   “Validator” means an entity operating a validator node connected solely to the Global Synchronizer.

